6:
I have not given up yet! I WILL have
my hordes of adoring fans!
15:
I mean, it's not an impossible goal.
People do tend to approach her
without special prompting.
24:
Let's list out everything we know so
far.
28:
Firstly, Inaho already has the
potential to become popular, so
there's no problem there.
37:
I do. It only makes logical sense
since you're cute by normal
standards.
42:
Ehehe, of course! I am cute! I am
positively adorable!
46:
And then she opens her mouth and
ruins that cuteness in one go. But we
can work on that.
50:
The other thing we should work out
is... Inaho, in what way do you want
to be popular?
55:
Well... I wish to be
appreciated—from a distance!
58:
You know... When someone
attractive walks by and heads turn?
I desire that sort of admiration!
62:
To be pampered and adored in a
harmless manner!
68: Yeah... Yeah! I totally get that!
72: You guys are off your rockers...
75:
The biggest problem is that you get
nervous, ain't it? Just let yourself go
with the flow and ride things out.
81:
I-I do not get nervous! I am Inaho
Tamamo, daughter of the legendary
Nine Tails!
86:
Uh-huh. Well, do whatever you want.
Figure out this problem yourself.
91: Hmph! You know what? I shall!
94: I am going to get a drink!
98:
Now you've gone and got her riled
up.
102:
Eh, she's the kinda person that
charges headfirst into something,
especially when she's bored. No way
she'll just sit around waiting for fans.
105:
You could learn a thing or two from
her about taking charge, honestly.
116:
You want me to join some sort of
event in your club?
119:
Only because you're special. Don't
go telling anyone else about it.
121:
If you think you're adult enough to
handle it... Swing on by.
130:
It is time! I shall attend this club
event and prove my worth!
134:
Heheh! Never again will someone
accuse me of being a coward!
141:
You've got nothing to worry about.
Once she puts her mind to
something, nobody can stop her.
144:
If anything, you should be more
worried for the people on the
receiving end of her crazy antics.
149:
Aaaand there she goes. She's just as
bad as Inaho sometimes.
152:
No way! The kid from lunch? You
actually showed up.
154:
Hehehe, if you wanna have some
fun so badly, just follow me.
168:
Woohoo! Who is ready to party
tonight?
175:
Ahahaha! Now that's what I call a
light show! You're one crazy gal!
179:
You got it! We shall dance to your
heart's content!
186:
Inaho is very Inaho, even without our
help.
191:
What is this? Have you all come to
party as well?
195:
The night is young! Join me in
dance, Stella.
